00:45:55.770 --> 00:45:57.770
After another.

00:45:57.770 --> 00:46:03.450
Tonight, when you watch Snick,

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:06.450
know that Pete is watching you watch Snick.

00:46:06.450 --> 00:46:08.450
Fair warning.

00:46:08.450 --> 00:46:14.000
Made you blink.

00:46:19.500 --> 00:46:21.500
Honest Abe Lincoln once said,

00:46:21.500 --> 00:46:24.500
a house divided against itself cannot stand.

00:46:26.500 --> 00:46:29.500
I'll bet his dad was a bowler too.

00:46:29.500 --> 00:46:31.500
It's hard to believe that our friendship

00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:34.500
was ending over a piece of molten rock.

00:46:34.500 --> 00:46:36.500
But the battle lines were drawn.

00:46:36.500 --> 00:46:38.500
Pete took his half of the bunk

00:46:38.500 --> 00:46:40.500
and moved to the basement.

00:46:40.500 --> 00:46:42.500
We were no longer talking.

00:46:42.500 --> 00:46:45.500
Any messages we had, we sent through Ellen.

00:46:45.500 --> 00:46:54.380
We even had a system

00:46:54.380 --> 00:46:56.380
so we didn't have to see each other at meals.

00:46:56.380 --> 00:47:09.760
Don, you have got to put a stop to this.

00:47:09.760 --> 00:47:11.760
It's gone too far.

00:47:11.760 --> 00:47:14.760
Maybe she's right, Dad.

00:47:14.760 --> 00:47:16.760
Maybe she is.

00:47:16.760 --> 00:47:18.760
And maybe she...

00:47:18.760 --> 00:47:22.200
Even with Artie guarding the house,

00:47:22.200 --> 00:47:25.200
the whole thing felt out of control.

00:47:25.200 --> 00:47:27.200
Careful, boy, careful.

00:47:27.200 --> 00:47:30.200
There are unfavorable omens in the air.

00:47:30.200 --> 00:47:38.310
You finished painting your dad's room yet?

00:47:38.310 --> 00:47:40.310
I couldn't.

00:47:40.310 --> 00:47:43.310
Pete wall-papered it last night and put down carpet.

00:47:43.310 --> 00:47:45.310
Ellen, this is insane.

00:47:45.310 --> 00:47:48.310
We even talked in two weeks.

00:47:48.310 --> 00:47:50.310
We've never gone that long without talking.

00:47:50.310 --> 00:47:54.420
War is ugly, Pete.

00:47:54.420 --> 00:47:56.420
But he's my best friend.

00:47:56.420 --> 00:47:58.420
I feel funny saying this,

00:47:58.420 --> 00:48:01.420
but maybe your best friendship wasn't meant to last forever.

00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:03.420
Friends do grow apart sometimes.

00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:05.420
And you are four years older.

00:48:05.420 --> 00:48:08.770
Think about it.

00:48:08.770 --> 00:48:10.770
Your brothers.

00:48:10.770 --> 00:48:12.770
How many brothers do you know who are best friends?

00:48:12.770 --> 00:48:19.540
And so the war raged on.

00:48:19.540 --> 00:48:23.540
My brother, one of the greatest natural generals ever born,

00:48:23.540 --> 00:48:26.540
began a full frontal assault.

00:48:28.020 --> 00:48:30.020
Pete says he's responsible,

00:48:30.020 --> 00:48:32.020
but last year he broke the hall vase.

00:48:32.020 --> 00:48:34.020
Pete says he loves his parents,

00:48:34.020 --> 00:48:36.020
but he didn't buy their anniversary card.

00:48:36.020 --> 00:48:38.020
So he left it and for the algebra final,

00:48:38.020 --> 00:48:40.020
Pete had to borrow notes,

