00:49:43.520 --> 00:49:50.350
Honey, uh...

00:49:50.350 --> 00:49:52.350
Something wrong?

00:49:52.350 --> 00:49:54.350
See, my mom had a metal plate in her head

00:49:54.350 --> 00:49:56.350
from an accident she had when she was a kid,

00:49:56.350 --> 00:49:58.350
and they both knew it would attract

00:49:58.350 --> 00:50:00.350
every lightning bolt for miles.

00:50:00.350 --> 00:50:02.350
Come inside, right now!

00:50:02.350 --> 00:50:04.350
Not until you stop this war!

00:50:04.350 --> 00:50:06.350
Not until you stop this war!

00:50:06.350 --> 00:50:08.350
I can't.

00:50:08.350 --> 00:50:10.350
He won't let me.

00:50:10.350 --> 00:50:12.350
If you don't stand up to your father,

00:50:12.350 --> 00:50:14.350
I'm going to blow myself to kingdom come.

00:50:14.350 --> 00:50:16.350
Dad had no choice.

00:50:16.350 --> 00:50:18.350
Maybe he didn't have the guts to face his dad,

00:50:18.350 --> 00:50:20.350
but he got another idea.

00:50:20.350 --> 00:50:22.350
Later that night,

00:50:22.350 --> 00:50:24.350
he snuck rolling thunder from the house

00:50:24.350 --> 00:50:28.910
and ran four hours

00:50:28.910 --> 00:50:30.910
to the Canadian Borger.

00:50:30.910 --> 00:50:32.910
Go on.

00:50:32.910 --> 00:50:34.910
I'm not going to let you down.

00:50:34.910 --> 00:50:36.910
I'm not going to let you down.

00:50:36.910 --> 00:50:46.180
Canadian Borger?

00:50:46.180 --> 00:50:48.180
Go on. What are you waiting for?

00:50:48.180 --> 00:50:52.580
You're free.

00:51:08.660 --> 00:51:12.220
You took it!

00:51:12.220 --> 00:51:14.220
Maybe it was stolen.

00:51:14.220 --> 00:51:16.220
I thought I heard a noise last night.

00:51:16.220 --> 00:51:18.220
Spunky.

00:51:18.220 --> 00:51:20.220
Have you done something?

00:51:20.220 --> 00:51:22.220
No.

00:51:22.220 --> 00:51:24.220
I know that look.

00:51:24.220 --> 00:51:26.220
You've done something.

00:51:26.220 --> 00:51:28.220
Tell Papa.

00:51:28.220 --> 00:51:30.220
What difference does it make?

00:51:30.220 --> 00:51:32.220
It's gone.

00:51:32.220 --> 00:51:34.220
Now we can get back to normal.

00:51:34.220 --> 00:51:36.220
But we all knew

00:51:36.220 --> 00:51:38.220
things would never be

00:51:38.220 --> 00:51:40.220
normal again.

00:51:40.220 --> 00:51:42.220
And that's when we heard it.

00:51:42.220 --> 00:51:46.340
Rolling thunder.

00:51:52.770 --> 00:51:54.770
No one knew how it got back,

00:51:54.770 --> 00:51:56.770
but one thing was certain.

00:51:56.770 --> 00:51:58.770
We had to settle this thing once

00:51:58.770 --> 00:52:00.770
and for all.

00:52:00.770 --> 00:52:02.770
Sometimes the only way

00:52:02.770 --> 00:52:04.770
to stop a war is to fight

00:52:04.770 --> 00:52:06.770
the bloodiest battle ever.

00:52:06.770 --> 00:52:08.770
A battle so gruesome there can only be

00:52:08.770 --> 00:52:10.770
one undisputed winner.

00:52:10.770 --> 00:52:12.770
Me and Pete were going to stare.

00:52:12.770 --> 00:52:14.770
And one and two.

00:52:14.770 --> 00:52:16.770
And one and two.

00:52:16.770 --> 00:52:18.770
Not only were the stakes

00:52:18.770 --> 00:52:20.770
higher than any other staring contest,

00:52:20.770 --> 00:52:22.770
but the only way to lose

00:52:22.770 --> 00:52:24.770
was to smile,

00:52:24.770 --> 00:52:26.770
and neither of us felt like smiling.

00:52:26.770 --> 00:52:28.770
Must destroy.

00:52:28.770 --> 00:52:30.770
Must destroy.

00:52:30.770 --> 00:52:32.770
Pete.

00:52:32.770 --> 00:52:34.770
Artie understood the contest

00:52:34.770 --> 00:52:36.770
could go on for weeks,

00:52:36.770 --> 00:52:38.770
even years.

00:52:38.770 --> 00:52:40.770
So he decided to come to our rescue.

00:52:40.770 --> 00:52:42.770
You know what I've come for,

00:52:42.770 --> 00:52:44.770
