01:32:49.040 --> 01:32:59.050
I call this story, the Tale of the Grims and Clown.

01:32:59.050 --> 01:33:02.170
Mike was a pretty average kid who worked a paper route.

01:33:02.170 --> 01:33:04.210
It was the day before his mother's birthday,

01:33:04.210 --> 01:33:07.210
and he managed to save $70 to buy her a gift.

01:33:07.210 --> 01:33:10.330
Come on, we've got to get to the store before it closes.

01:33:10.330 --> 01:33:13.530
Go yourself, I'm watching something.

01:33:13.530 --> 01:33:15.450
Sam, it's mom's birthday tomorrow.

01:33:15.450 --> 01:33:17.170
We have to get her a present together.

01:33:17.170 --> 01:33:18.570
Let's go.

01:33:18.570 --> 01:33:21.050
Go where?

01:33:21.050 --> 01:33:22.610
Um, skating.

01:33:22.610 --> 01:33:25.050
Skating, just for a little while.

01:33:25.050 --> 01:33:31.460
Yeah, wouldn't want to get too chilly skating, would we?

01:33:31.460 --> 01:33:35.140
Keep your eye on your brother and be home at six.

01:33:35.140 --> 01:33:43.830
OK, skates.

01:33:43.830 --> 01:33:46.070
I guess we'll need these, won't we?

01:33:46.070 --> 01:34:17.650
Skating.

01:34:17.650 --> 01:34:20.930
Sorry, here, I'll get the door.

01:34:20.930 --> 01:34:22.770
Have a nice day.

01:34:22.770 --> 01:34:26.100
Bye.

01:34:26.100 --> 01:34:27.500
What a bunch of crud.

01:34:27.500 --> 01:34:28.700
Don't find anything here.

01:34:28.700 --> 01:34:29.900
Sam.

01:34:29.900 --> 01:34:31.500
I'm going to the toy store.

01:34:31.500 --> 01:34:33.100
I'm supposed to watch you.

01:34:33.100 --> 01:34:35.100
No sweat, watch me leave.

01:34:35.100 --> 01:34:36.700
Sam, we've got to get mom's present.

01:34:36.700 --> 01:34:38.820
No, you've got to get mom's present.

01:34:38.820 --> 01:34:39.700
I'm out of here.

01:34:39.700 --> 01:34:40.600
Forget it.

01:34:40.600 --> 01:34:41.500
It's too late and up.

01:34:41.500 --> 01:34:43.660
I'm only going next door.

01:34:43.660 --> 01:34:45.180
We'll just go next door, all right?

01:34:45.180 --> 01:34:47.260
And don't leave till I come get you.

01:34:47.260 --> 01:35:07.160
Yes, ma'am.

01:35:07.160 --> 01:35:08.280
100 bucks.

01:35:08.280 --> 01:35:31.400
All right.

01:35:31.400 --> 01:35:32.680
Um, yeah.

01:35:32.680 --> 01:35:36.560
Um, I'm looking for a birthday gift for my mom.

01:35:36.560 --> 01:35:38.240
I see.

01:35:38.240 --> 01:35:42.960
Well, my friend, how much are you willing to spend?

01:35:42.960 --> 01:35:46.160
Um, 70, $70.

01:35:46.160 --> 01:35:50.260
Let me see now.

01:35:50.260 --> 01:35:52.540
Oh, yeah.

01:35:52.540 --> 01:35:55.500
How about this little prize?

01:35:55.500 --> 01:36:00.770
It's perfect.

01:36:00.770 --> 01:36:03.920
Sam, what do you think?

01:36:03.920 --> 01:36:05.520
Sam?

01:36:05.520 --> 01:36:08.680
It's OK.

01:36:08.680 --> 01:36:09.580
I'll take it.

01:36:09.580 --> 01:36:11.950
How much is it?

01:36:11.950 --> 01:36:15.790
For you, $50.

01:36:15.790 --> 01:36:33.070
All right.

01:36:33.070 --> 01:36:35.030
Is there a problem?

01:36:35.030 --> 01:36:38.910
Um, well, my money's gone.

01:36:38.910 --> 01:36:41.910
Well, I must have left it at home.

01:36:41.910 --> 01:36:55.630
I'm sure I brought it.

01:36:55.630 --> 01:36:57.510
I see.

01:36:57.510 --> 01:37:02.820
Maybe another time.

01:37:02.820 --> 01:37:06.720
Sam, have you seen my money?

01:37:06.720 --> 01:37:13.370
Sam, where did you get this?

01:37:13.370 --> 01:37:15.210
The toy store.

01:37:15.210 --> 01:37:16.770
With what money?

01:37:16.770 --> 01:37:18.010
My birthday money.

01:37:18.010 --> 01:37:19.250
You spent that on a bike.

01:37:19.250 --> 01:37:20.810
I had some left over.

01:37:20.810 --> 01:37:21.770
No, you didn't.

01:37:21.770 --> 01:37:24.290
You spent it all.

01:37:24.290 --> 01:37:27.350
You stole my money.

01:37:27.350 --> 01:37:29.070
Let's consider it a loan.

01:37:29.070 --> 01:37:32.150
Sam, that money was for mom's birthday gift.

01:37:32.150 --> 01:37:33.790
It was all I had.

01:37:33.790 --> 01:37:36.110
Oh, well, too late now.

01:37:36.110 --> 01:37:36.750
No, it's not.

01:37:36.750 --> 01:37:38.070
We're getting it back.

01:37:38.070 --> 01:37:46.110
Do we just return something?

01:37:46.110 --> 01:37:49.190
Oh, well, guess it, Mr. Chance.

01:37:49.190 --> 01:37:50.150
No, I didn't.

01:37:50.150 --> 01:37:52.950
Come on.

01:37:52.950 --> 01:37:53.990
Can I pay you tomorrow?

01:37:53.990 --> 01:37:56.630
I swear, please, it's my mom's birthday.

01:37:56.630 --> 01:37:57.470
Sorry.

01:37:57.470 --> 01:38:00.830
Come back when you got the money.

01:38:00.830 --> 01:38:03.350
Does this mean we can go home now?

01:38:03.350 --> 01:38:05.750
Do you know what happens to bad kids?

01:38:05.750 --> 01:38:07.710
I mean really bad kids like you.

01:38:07.710 --> 01:38:10.110
No, why don't you tell me?

01:38:10.110 --> 01:38:13.070
Whenever you get snotty with somebody,

01:38:13.070 --> 01:38:16.670
whenever you hurt someone, whenever you're selfish

01:38:16.670 --> 01:38:17.630
or insult somebody.

01:38:17.630 --> 01:38:19.390
Yeah, yeah, I better not pout.

01:38:19.390 --> 01:38:22.470
I better not shout, because Santa Claus is coming to town.

01:38:22.470 --> 01:38:29.170
Sam, whenever you're bad, and that means when you steal,

01:38:29.170 --> 01:38:31.970
Crimson Clown is watching you.

01:38:31.970 --> 01:38:34.960
Ooh.

01:38:34.960 --> 01:38:37.080
Watch out, Sam, or it'll get you.

01:38:37.080 --> 01:38:39.200
Ooh, I'm scared.

01:38:39.200 --> 01:38:40.760
Don't believe me?

01:38:40.760 --> 01:38:58.450
You'll see.

01:38:58.450 --> 01:39:00.570
Now we're late, and mom's going to be tipped.

01:39:00.570 --> 01:39:02.490
Well, who cares?

01:39:02.490 --> 01:39:03.770
You should, because of you.

01:39:03.770 --> 01:39:05.210
We don't have a gift for her.

01:39:05.210 --> 01:39:06.690
Just put some cash in a car.

01:39:06.690 --> 01:39:07.650
She'll be happy.

01:39:07.650 --> 01:39:09.410
You stole my cash, remember?

01:39:09.410 --> 01:39:11.610
Why don't you ask your pal to Crimson Clown?

01:39:11.610 --> 01:39:18.940
Come on, let's go.

01:39:18.940 --> 01:39:33.430
Tell mom we'll be right down.

01:39:33.430 --> 01:39:34.630
Yeah, whatever.

01:39:34.630 --> 01:39:39.500
Where have you been?

01:39:39.500 --> 01:39:41.620
Look at the time.

01:39:41.620 --> 01:39:43.260
Where's Michael?

01:39:43.260 --> 01:39:45.580
Um, upstairs.

01:39:45.580 --> 01:39:51.660
I told you to be back at six.

01:39:51.660 --> 01:39:54.460
I'm sorry, mom.

01:39:54.460 --> 01:39:56.260
I wanted to come home.

01:39:56.260 --> 01:39:58.020
But Mike said he wanted to see his friends,

01:39:58.020 --> 01:40:02.180
